<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                    <head>No. 661.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-19"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 19, 1880</date>.
                            (Received May 6.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 219.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I think it proper to communicate to you, as
                        matter of information, that Mr. C. J. Bandman (of New York, I think) has
                        contracted with this government for the construction and operation of two
                        prospective railways: one from La Guayra to Caracas, and the other from
                        Puerto Cabello to Valencia.</p>
                    <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JEHU BAKER.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>